ion of CO2, are sequential in nature; by contrast, they are\ncoupled in each of the two subsequent hydride and proton transfers to reduce\nformic acid and formaldehyde.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Aug 2014 21:53:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-20"}
