y. In the framework\nof the latter scenario the $^{15}$N($\\alpha$,$\\gamma$)$^{19}$F and the\n$^{19}$F($\\alpha$,p)$^{22}$Ne reactions show the largest effects on fluorine\nnucleosynthesis. The presence of poorly known low energy resonances make such a\nscenario, even if unlikely, possible. We plan to directly measure these\nresonances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Aug 2014 12:02:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-10-15"}
